24/06/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder said Wednesday (23 June) that an agreement has been reached with French President Jacques Chirac to launch EU accession negotiations with Turkey if the EU Commission's progress report on Turkey is favourable.
Meanwhile Dutch Foreign Minister Bernard Bot insisted that the decision on Turkey would be transparent and fair.
The Netherlands assumes the rotating EU presidency in July.
Turkish local press reports cited diplomatic sources as saying Ankara expects EU accession negotiations to begin when the UK assumes the rotating presidency in July 2005.
In other news, Turkey and the "Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus" (TRNC) signed a funding agreement Wednesday.
Turkey will provide $346.6m in financial aid to the TRNC this year.
(Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2, AFP - 23/06/04)
